quran[10]{c,v,t}:
  16,41,"As for those who, after persecution, migrated from their homes for the cause of God, We will provide them with a goodly abode in this life: but truly the reward of the Hereafter will be greater, if they only knew it"
  16,42,They are the ones who are steadfast and put their trust in their Lord
  16,43,"Before you also the messengers We sent were but [mortal] men to whom We vouchsafed revelation. Ask the People of the Book, if you do not know"
  16,44,"[We sent them] with clear signs and scriptures. We have sent down the Reminder to you, to enable you to make clear to mankind what has been sent down to them, so that they may reflect upon it"
  16,45,"Do those who devise evil plans feel secure that God will not make them sink into the land, or that a punishment will not come upon them from where they least expect"
  16,46,Or that He will not seize them suddenly in their daily activities and they will not be able to frustrate Him
  16,47,"Or that He will not punish them by giving them a fright? Indeed, your Lord is kind and merciful"
  16,48,"Have they not observed the things God has created, casting their shadows right and left, prostrating themselves before God in all humility"
  16,49,"Everything in the heavens and all the creatures on the earth prostrate themselves before God, as do the angels, and they do not behave proudly"
  16,50,"they fear their Lord above them, and do what they are commanded"